8 §5233.2. Protection of freedom of worship; limitation of liability
9 A. The Legislature of Louisiana finds that houses of worship are private
10 property dedicated to the free exercise of religion, that religious assemblies are
11 protected by the Constitution of the United States and the Constitution of Louisiana,
12 and that the right to exclude disruptive and potentially violent individuals may be
13 necessary to facilitate the free exercise of religion. The Legislature of Louisiana
14 further finds that clarification of existing statutory authority is in the furtherance of
15 justice and the free exercise of religion.
16 B. Any religious leader, authorized security team member, or person
17 lawfully present and permitted on the premises of a house of worship may request
18 that a person leave the premises if the person is committing criminal trespass
19 pursuant to R.S. 14:63 or is engaged in a substantial disruption. Such request shall
20 constitute notice for purposes of criminal trespass law.
